    "file": "source/extensions/filters/http/fault/fault_filter.cc",
    "line": 156,
    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "Incorrect return status when delay is injected in fault filter. The code returns Http::FilterHeadersStatus::Continue when a delay is set up, but should return Http::FilterHeadersStatus::StopIteration. According to the filter specification, when a delay is injected, the filter must pause the filter chain (StopIteration) until the delay timer fires. Returning Continue allows the request to proceed immediately, bypassing the injected delay and violating the fault injection contract.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/source/extensions/filters/http/fault/fault_filter.cc
+++ b/source/extensions/filters/http/fault/fault_filter.cc
@@ -153,7 +153,7 @@ Http::FilterHeadersStatus FaultFilter::decodeHeaders(Http::RequestHeaderMap& hea
   maybeSetupResponseRateLimit(headers);

   if (maybeSetupDelay(headers)) {
-    return Http::FilterHeadersStatus::Continue;
+    return Http::FilterHeadersStatus::StopIteration;
   }

   if (maybeDoAbort(headers)) {
"
  }
]

